description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3gqoq","text":"This protocol generates sponges (Halichondria panicea) with a disturbed microbiome under controlled experimental conditions, in order to study bacterial recolonization dynamics. Bacteria-bacteria interactions can be analysed with this set-up within the host environment aiming at a better understanding of sponge-microbe symbiosis in vivo. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":33,"length":20},{"style":"italic","offset":331,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"62eho","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"auns0","text":"It is divided into the sections 1) preparation, 2) antibiotic treatment and recovery phase, 3) recolonization with the natural microbiome and 4) sampling.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"77n67","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3h9bu","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1rth1","text":"The flow-through set-up (Figure) consists of 32 x 500 mL modified Erlenmeyer flasks distributed on 4 shelfs. Each set of 8 flasks is supplied with fresh, sterile filtered artificial seawater from one 20 L carboy.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":23}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c007","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"98nb1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8not1","text":"The culture flasks are customized flow-through Erlenmeyer flasks (500 mL) that are fully autoclavable and re-usable (Figure). The flasks are closed with a hollow glass stopper. Water is exchanged via a hose barb and attached glass tube reaching near the bottom of the Erlenmeyer flask for water inflow, and a hose barb on the opposite side for water outflow. A thread with a screw cap and silicone septum allows for sampling culture water with a sterile syringe and needle without opening the flasks.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":19}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fsl1g","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dr9jv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9k13v","text":"Water flow-through is realized by GHL2 pumps that pump water from a 20 L source tank into the Erlenmeyer flasks; the replaced water is collected in 10 L canisters. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ei1dr","text":"Important! Calibrate each pump head prior to an experiment via the GHL software.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fmku7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"32ufm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e4tp7","text":"The gnotobiotic chambers are equipped with an air filtration system (Expansion Electronic CP500/SNATURE SYSTEM) constantly removing microorganisms from the air. The temperature and light regime can be chosen according to the season. Surface area is minimized and regularly surface sterilized (Curacid Medical wipes). All material is either autoclavable, sterile packed or sterilizable by surface sterilization prior to entering the room. Access is restricted and only allowed with lab coat, gloves and shoe covers. A transitioning zone in front of the gnotobiotic chambers provides space for changing, storage of additional material, cleaning of material etc..","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":24}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fded8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"edvh0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"857g9","text":"The experiment can be set up one day prior to the start (start = placing sponges in the flasks), but some things have to be prepared 1-2 weeks in advance (start with section \"preparation\"). {"blocks":[{"key":"2v3o","text":"Sterile filtered artificial seawater (F-ASW)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":44}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d07au","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ds3n7","text":"F-ASW should be prepared every day during the antibiotic treatment and every second day during the recovery phase and recolonization","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e8d7o","text":"Fill a 100 l barrel with destilled water while continuously adding 1.5 kg artificial seasalt","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7ffmm","text":"Dissolution can be sped up by adding a water pump into the barrel to mix the water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"53hnh","text":"Mix well! Check salinity at bottom and top of the barrel and prevent foramtion of a salinity gradient. Slowly add missing salt until the desired salinity is reached","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"62tu0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4ft57","text":"Since the salinity constantly fluctuates in the Baltic Sea, we choose the ambient salinity on the starting day of each experiment (between 14 and 18 PSU)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6l267","text":"Connect autoclaved stainless steel filter holder (142 mm) unit to pump and fill 4 autoclaved 20 l carboys with F-ASW","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cvgq9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"agtg1","text":"When all carboys are filled, stop water pump and rinse it in fresh water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"co9tc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fmbgi","text":"Rinse filter unit and change filter paper; autoclave including silicone tube for the next filtration","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dosr9","text":"Add 40 ml Nannochloropsis salina stock solution to each 20 l carboy","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":10,"length":23}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7ol4k","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ffaov","text":"During antibiotic treatment, add 20 ml per antibiotic to each 20 l carboy. The final working concentrations will be:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d61g4","text":"50 mg/l Rifampicin ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8g1n9","text":"50 mg/l Ampicillin ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"beg4u","text":"50 mg/l Nalidixic acid","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d4u7l","text":"50 mg/l Neomycin","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dr5uu","text":"2 mg/l Polymixin B","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aet5q","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"e3s66","text":"Mix well (by rolling closed carboys)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6qfs7","text":"After use, rinse carboys twice with fresh water and autoclave for the next use","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6r567","text":"MB medium","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d21h4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b4h1m","text":"Prepare 15 g/l Difco agar and 37.5 g MarineBroth in 1 l destilled water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"14d3o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fklig","text":"Prepare ~350 plates per experiment (= 10 bottles of MB medium) and store at 4°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"c3182","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5kf4k","text":"Cook in water bath for 10-15 min to dissolve medium","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e8d0r","text":"Autoclave and store at 60°C until pouring plates","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dn0eb","text":"Pour plates under biosafety cabinet and store upside down at 4°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"csmq1","text":"CMF-ASW (Calcium-Magnesium-free artificial seawater) after Rottmann et al. 1987","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":79}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6bvhd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4an82","text":"Prepare e.g. 10 l as a stock and autoclave in portions of 500 ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1omb6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d88er","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6f6v5","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"bue7v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"safety","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"add95","text":"attention! The recipe for CMF-ASW is thought for marine organisms. Since we are working on sponges from brackish water here, dilute the stock 1:1 before autoclaving","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8jd4","text":"For 1 l stock solution:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"940mo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"46dfa","text":"27 g NaCl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"eb4c","text":"1 g Na2SO4","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":6,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":9,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1r4hm","text":"0.8 g KCl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9uv5v","text":"0.18 g NaHCO3","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":12,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"78l1l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6qclc","text":"add 1 l MilliQ water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f7nc2","text":"Dilute stock 1:1 with MilliQ water and autoclave in portions of 500 ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"bquns","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ajhjp","text":"Can be stored at RT, but it is used ice-cold. Put bottles in freezer 1 h before they are needed","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ftke4","text":"Antibiotic treatment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":20}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b8f87","text":"During the first four days of the experiment prepare ASW with antibiotics and change water source daily","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"975dj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"evqmr","text":"    ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"2398n","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"euovm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b4jl","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"86557D3021CB11ECB21567F0CFEA5738","height":194,"id":313179,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7of5o","text":"Timeline of the antibiotic treatment. T0 = start of the experiment; T4 = end of the antibiotic treatment; T11 = end of the recovery phase and start of the recoloniziation. Figure created with Biorender.com","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":[]},"mime":"image/jpeg","original_name":"AntibioticExposureExperiment.jpeg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt47be7b7.jpg","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt45be7b7.jpg","type":1,"webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt46be7b7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jt44be7b7.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1bp2p","text":"Start pumps on the first day prior to placing sponges in the Erlenmeyer flasks","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"26gj1","text":"Set pumps to 150 doses/day of 12 ml to exchange the volume of each bottle 3.5 times per day","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":12,"length":24}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3fve2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1lfhg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c1m3b","text":"When Erlenmeyer flasks are filled, add one sponge in each Erlenmeyer flask (about 3x3x3 cm)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d7ius","text":"Start the experiment early in the morning","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"emduj","text":"Prepare fresh antibiotic water and change carboys daily to prevent degradation and loss of function of antibiotics","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqnl4","text":"Antibiotic wash-out","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":19}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"a5fl7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"bmuir","text":"In the afternoon of T4 start wash-out of antibiotics by exchanging the carboys with ASW+antibiotics to carboys with ASW only","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"do12h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3bisj","text":"Flush the Erlenmeyer flasks several times with 250 ml fresh ASW each (by programming the pumps to dose 250 ml. Attention! The GHL2 pumps are not designed to continuously run; after each flush they need to stop for at least 15 min)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7l581","text":"Since Rifampicin is coloured bright orange, you clearly see the reduction of antibiotics in the water by flushing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4h53s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3s8hc","text":"Aim at completely clear culture water until the next morning to prevent remaining antibiotics at low concentrations","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"586rn","text":"It helps to manually pour out water (without opening the Erlenmeyer; simply tilt the bottle and empty it via the outflow barb) and reduce the water level to about 200 ml before flushing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7pmpg","text":"Recovery phase","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"5t9a1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"5k063","text":"During the recovery phase, exchange the water source every second day with freshly filtered ASW","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"e59n3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8a8tb","text":"Set the pumps to 100 doses/day of 10 ml to exchange to volume of each bottle twice per day","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":17,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"38p54","text":"Differential centrifugation","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":27}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9se9p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dvuvg","text":"To prepare a bacterial inoculum for recolonization with the natural microbiome dissociate fresh, healthy sponges","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3dtlj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"brklk","text":"The volume of sponge tissue should match the volume of sponge that you want to recolonize","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9fpmn","text":"Remove large pieces of algae and place sponges in a beaker with sterile, ice-cold CMF-ASW for 5 min to remove loosely attached bacteria","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"34d82","text":"Replace CMF-ASW","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7l9dq","text":"Cut sponge tissue with a razor and forceps in a petri dish with sterile, ice-cold CMF-ASW","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7kqbs","text":"Only process a small piece at a time and try to keep tissue submerged","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3t6mt","text":"Remove algae or other non-sponge material","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7f05h","text":"Transfer the pieces into 50 ml polypropylene tubes filled with ~30 ml sterile, ice-cold CMF-ASW and keep them on ice during the process","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"f7ru2","text":"Add no more than 10 ml sponge tissue","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"beoak","text":"Top up tubes until 50 ml with sterile, ice-cold CMF-ASW","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ch57q","text":"Incubate tubes on ice on an orbital shaker at 200 rpm for 20 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6lihn","text":"Filter through 40 µm cell strainer in fresh 50 ml polypropylene tubes, squeeze remaining tissue with forceps","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8acod","text":"Top up until 50 ml with sterile, ice-cold CMF-ASW","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9kj5q","text":"Centrifuge for 20 min at 700 g and 4°C to remove sponge cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8e9a0","text":"Transfer supernatant to a fresh 50 ml polypropylene tube and discard the sponge cell pellet","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9og7p","text":"Centrifuge supernatant for 15 min at 4000 g and 4°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"at9mp","text":"Resuspend the pellet in ~5 ml CMF-ASW and pool the bacteria fraction from several tubes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fj1ej","text":"This is the recolonization inoculum. Keep on ice!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c2qtf","text":"Proceed as quickly as possible to prevent dying of bacteria. Always keep on ice!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dovt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9us06","text":"First recolonize, but keep a few milliliters to sample (step 12)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1dk6e","text":"Recolonization","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9s7os","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8m6bc","text":"Recolonize sponges by injection of 2 ml recolonization mix with sterile syringes and needles","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"24grp","text":"Inject gradually and change location 5 times per sponge to distribute the inoculum throughout the whole animal","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ahqef","text":"For the control treatment, use a sham control with 2 ml sterile CMF-ASW per sponge","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9mm53","text":"Viability and composition of inoculum","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":37}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2pusm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7af9c","text":"Take different samples to ensure viability of inoculum and analyse bacterial composition later with qPCR and amplicon sequencing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bjsie","text":"Plate 100 µl pure inoculum, 1:10, 1:100 and 1:1000 dilution on MB agar plates at incubate at 25°C for 1 day","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2j8ac","text":"Check lower dilutions after 7 days","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aeq4k","text":"Freeze several aliquots of 1 ml pure inoculation mix in cryovials and flash freeze in liquid nitrogen","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4478t","text":"Store at -80°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7qmmn","text":"Filter 2 x 2 ml inoculum mix onto 0.22 µm filter with a reusable syringe filter holder (diameter 25 mm), store filter in cryovials and flash freeze in liquid nitrogen","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ojjd","text":"Store at -80°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dvn47","text":"Fix 2 x 1.8 ml inoculum mix with 0.2 ml Glutaraldehyde+Paraformaldehyde (final concentration 0.01 % and 1 %)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"f74qk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"34ste","text":"Fix for 10 min at RT","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"f5maf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"acpso","text":"Freeze at -80°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"16dpi","text":"Repeat recolonization three times within 48 h to ensure transfer of bacteria","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":76}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dq93a","text":"Plating of culture water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":24}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2thut","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ctsbi","text":"To monitor bacterial growth in the Erlenmeyer flasks, culture water is plated every 2-3 days. The sterile filtered ASW and the food stock solutions should be plated before the start and at least once during the experiment to ensure sterility","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aqlu1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"5iskl","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"n220","text":"Sample ~1 ml culture water from 4 replicate tanks per treatment via the silicone septum with a sterile needle and syringe. Rinse syringe once with culture water before taking the sample and take care to do it very slowly, so the sponge does not get kicked around by the water current","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aom95","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"78pug","text":"Store samples in fridge no longer than 3 h","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b8jaf","text":"Under the clean bench: prepare dilution series by pipetting 100 µL culture water and 900 µL saline (1:10) and repeat twice until a dilution of 1:1000 that is used for plating","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"69ppu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9kvj1","text":"Mix well!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2q4o9","text":"Plate 100 µL of the 1:1000 dilution in triplicates on MB agar plates; use glass spatula (sterilize by dipping in ethanol and burning, cool down) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"af6nf","text":"Wrap plates with parafilm and incubate upside down at 25°C for 7 days","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"oicm","text":"Count colony forming units (CFUs)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
